SlZuUwQ7ccrP13u56Fbcdw.text: Now usually the quality of mexican food here would be super a-okay and nothing to rave about - however, having tried mexican at a few other places where it was AWFUL - this is place is pretty good for a mexican joint in Singapore. I had the veggie enchilada dish and I was not dissapointed with the serving size. Both of my friends got meat dishes that had large portions as well, so we were all really happy about it. Overall, food was good. Not amazing, but you leave satisfied.Our margarita drinks were not lame either - and were strong enough.They also didn't skimp on the sour cream and guac so we really appreciated that.

IIZ02TBYKdDngPI9Mt2d-w.text: Dempsey Hill pricey but probably the best texmex I have had consistently have eaten in Singapore.  Ambience gets you out of the humidity.  Margaritas are good not great,  but my "great" is in either San Antonio or Houston on account of the those Rio Bravo limes.

-Dk3ncScJSCO3aqhMGLlnA.text: Overpriced and mediocre quality. However, this is pretty standard for Mexican in Singapore, so take that for what it's worth.

JjS0TEaRg0DA4W_XnPpdjg.text: Taco salad was very nice ($19), but the carne asada ($49, signature dish) was not so good - the meat was low quality and stringy. We had to send it back to be cooked more (I.e., we had wanted medium, had to go well as the meat wasn't good enough for well). Service was quite slow, with them not checking on our meal or refilling water. I ordered ice water, and water came without ice. Took over ten minutes for the check after we requested it. Ambience was nice. Will try again, curious about burritos and fajitas.

1xNzjBDRUX72ZSKjLeaHYQ.text: If I were judging this restaurant on curve and gave it bonus points for being halfway around the world from Mexico, it would probably get 4 stars.Pros:-The menu is small, but a pretty good approximation of Mexican restaurants in North America-The chips were good; the salsa was excellent-The margaritas were excellent as wellCons:-The carnitas tasted pretty bland-The restaurant is expensive, even by Singaporean standardsI would probably go back, but I certainly will wait until I have a strong hankering for Mexican food before I do so.

xfVfai-9U5lIP9uPwKF2mA.text: Relatively bland overpriced Tex-mex. Sauce for both red and green enchiladas was in desperate need of chili powder, cumin, and garlic powder to add flavor. The red sauce was simply puréed tomatoes (seriously...it was that lacking). Luckily, the meat (both chicken and beef) was good...not great....but good and not dried out, so the meal was edible.  Side rice was not Mexican or Spanish or Latin in taste.  Sadly, the best part of my meal was the side of black beans. For a minimum of S$18++/a dish I would expect higher efforts.  If they hadn't put a couple slices of jalapenos on the top, the dish would be totally lacking in flavor.  If the restaurant would simply invest in a few spices (go on and add it to the guac too...it sure needs them), the meal could be WORLDS better.   I admit that it is hard to find authentic Tex-mex here in Singapore, but pretty much every other place I have tasted on the island is better.  I didn't opt to try the margaritas (wow...highway robbery).  I will make my own at home!

9iK-2BgVPxOj8s5y8p4rlQ.text: Realistic Mexican food served here.  A nice place to come for a home-sick Californian needing some comida Mexicana.  Good variety of food, refried beans could be better but it's ok.  This location at Dempsey Hill and atmosphere is very nice, always enjoy it here.  A little pricey but it is Singapore after all.  But I always drink Tiger beer, not Corona.

7yG77ZIF1uLGibycYLDv0w.text: Having spent a lot of time in Mexico, I found it a bit curious to be eating  Mexican food in Singapore but, my team was flying off so there we were. It was like being in Mexico except in Singapore. The fajitas was delicious, I love their margarita presentation (basically served in a bottle of patron) and their chips and other dishes were pretty good. It's pricey though..esp for Mexican food but hey, if you're in Singapore and you have a craving for Mexican food, this place is spot on.

uMP53e1w8fuCUYEb5AsAQA.text: Hands down the best Mexican I've had in Singapore! Every single dish is great, especially their hot pan beef fajitas, beyond words! Felt like I went on to heaven and came back to margarita's... the first bite of beef was incredible (eat it with the onion). AMAZING. Had their chicken enchiladas, was a 4star for me compared to the general ones out there. Also had the best nachos here (the one with black beans and guacamole). Ordered a virgin mojito, can't go wrong with that. the concoction was balanced and perfect for if you find the green chilli spicy. Their spice level is very manageable relative to other Mexican restaurants. Will definitely come back again and again :)

jEBtm1D6ugMUlXZR3dCIIw.text: Have been so many times and will continue to go back.  Greatest Mexican food I can find in Singapore.

pedtYwONt9wWFGEERCS3LA.text: Sometimes I eat here and the food is great, however last time I ate there I got sick. I had the chimichangas and was rushed to the toilet moments later. Tried to tell them it was far too greasy and not looking so great however they did not offer to make again or have discount. Their margarita pitchers are a great choice if you are having a large group together though. And their fajitas are a good choice. Also good menu for children.

ZKmJi8KQr9PiUW2xIepHzA.text: Had dinner with friends here a couple of nights ago. I had been here ages ago and didn't have a good impression but I was pleasantly surprised this time.We ordered a pitcher of tamarind margaritas, which was refreshing. We had nachos with melted cheese, with a hint of chili. It was warm, tasty and a good portion  for 3-4 people. The chicken taco salad was OK,  but the Christmas special menu item crab au gratin was delicious. It came with tortilla and a sauce that tasted like olives. For dessert we had toffee pudding with chili. It was good. Service was friendly and fast. I don't think that this is authentic Mexican food. It's more Tex-Mex. Still enjoyable though, with a nice ambience.

voM2Nuq8C4CLRvoJ2omdxQ.text: What could've been an enjoyable dinner on Cinco de Mayo ended with the hostess chasing after us for items left off the bill. While we were patient with the disorganized service staff, serving all entrees at different times and understanding when they brought an entirely incorrect bill to our table- upwards of $400. It was corrected, we paid and sat for another 10 mins before leaving the restaurant. She then came after us, apologizing for their obvious mistake and offering no consolation- even when I mentioned that it was my birthday and suggested the drinks (one pitcher of Margaritas!) could be comped on the House. What a waste of a holiday- terrible service and mediocre food

6IeiV6S-GL79jLsmzc3GgQ.text: Recently refurbished, it has a nice feel, sat at the bar and had margaritas, great service, nachos and salsa really good, got a table for dinner and had the beef tacos which were excellent, mixed fajitas really tasty, an excellent evening, great place and great Mexican food

doCkil8HjxUYMSepw-qwEA.text: First time I can remember having good tasting Mexican food in Asia.  Certain one nothing like this in Hong Kong and I haven't found anything close in Singapore until now. Guacamole was great. Enjoyed the Chicken burrito, very nice presentation, as well as the red snapper my wife had. Probably my favorite was the tortilla soup, really tasty. As could be expected in this location, Dempsey Hill, it's pricey, but worth it for something this good in Singapore.

KBwdmxwfzkeBN5ZWFsPohw.text: Probably the best Mexican food in Singapore but the best thing about it is that they have gluten free options.

KsyB0pwsMgiQh0LSGnCQkA.text: This is probably the worst service I've had at any place I've eaten at in Singapore. Poor service and horrible queso are not going to bring me back any time soon. Won't be coming back ever!

_15w-T0wZKM0h5C8lzc9Cw.text: Had heard a lot of good things about this place but the food sadly didn't live up to expectations. Had the nachos which were not that bad. My main course was the lime chicken with chipotle sauce. The sauce and the accompanying rice and beans were fine but the chicken was too rubbery.

aKMs-ZRnnw65K2UFYOCCbg.text: An upscale version of Chipotle, in terms of quality and portion (well unless you've mastered the skill of maximizing your burrito bowl :P) I would recommend this restaurant if you're dining with a party of 3+ so you can share and enjoy the various Mexican dishes Magarita's offers. Some of my personal favorites are the taco salad that comes with generous amounts of chicken, veggies, cheese, and kidney beans (though it seems like they've cut back on the amount of black beans served in return) and the US prime rib, which is very tender and well marinated. The crab meat quesadilla is mediocre; there was too much cheese and scarce amounts of crab.

OJH1-R7GG59TcY5H-rnxZA.text: Very interesting place..nice set up and ambience and we were pleasantly surprised to find oysters in this place. The enchiladas and quesadillas were pretty good and so were the desserts - tiramisu..however they close fairly early at 10:30 pm!

photos.caption: Photo of Margarita's Dempsey Hill - Singapore, Singapore. Fresh oysters!

b63XFuSGTKMZmc67nYGmFw.text: Heard a lot about this place and decided to give it a try   Being from California in USA, I am always looking for good Margaritas and Mexican food.  Well, good blended Margaritas.....they should be for the price $76 for a pitcher that serves about 6 small glasses.  After ordering drinks, my pocketbook had a hard time opening wider to order food, so ordered chips & salsa and cheese taquitos.  The salsa was okay and fixed up to taste authentic, but definitely from a can and chips were warm and tasty.  The taquitos were good and covered in tasty salsa w/ dollops of sour cream & guacamole.The atmosphere was pleasant and inviting.  The music started off with Latin music, but over time got mixed up w/ Caribbean steel drum.  The wait staff was attentive and pleasant.  The extra star is for them.All in all pleasant experience.

Wo2tqH-3H_mqaLwIem7c_g.text: This is a review of a dinner date at Margarita's at Dempsey Hill.My date had an evening class.  We first met at Crystal Jade in Holland Village.  But they were too busy.  It was already beyond 10.  We decided to just go to Dempsey and pick a place.tinyurl.com/b9cl5fuShe suggested La Salsa.  But I've already been there.  I knew Margarita's was close by and countered with it.When we arrived, we were told that we had to order ASAP.  They were closing soon and this was the last round of orders.  They meant this too.  Just after we were seated, they were at our table and it was clear they wanted us to order.  I believe restaurants should either be open or they should be closed. Throughout our meal, the staff was friendly but rushed.  For this, I have deducted one star from their overall review.The ambiance is great. I actually really liked the room.  It has very high ceilings. The earthen tones make for a warm inviting environment.  There are lots of paintings on the wall.  It would be a great space for a party.tinyurl.com/bayzxalWe each ordered a cocktail.  I had a frozen lime margarita.  She had a frozen strawberry daiquiri.  My margarita was a tad on the bitter side.  Outside of that, it reminded me of a margarita made with basic margarita mix.tinyurl.com/bx6ezg6tinyurl.com/as8a663The food was average to relatively good.Chicken Fajitas -  I could almost cut and paste my review of the steak fajitas from La Salsa.  They were very generous with the chicken.  It did come on a sizzling platter.  The seasoning seemed like something straight out of pre-made spice mix.  They were not nearly as generous with the condiments.  Plus, these also appeared to be straight out of cans, jars, or bottles.  The guacamole had no texture to it.  The salsa was no better that Tostito's.  They did not provide beans or rice.  If you are going to charge $30+ for chicken fajitas, they should darn well come with beans and rice.  The tortillas were well heated.In the end, these were decent fajitas.  If the salsa and guacamole had been better, it could have made a big difference. tinyurl.com/a6h7mohCondiments:tinyurl.com/balvrr8Margarita Chicken - My dinner date ordered their Margarita Chicken.  I did not try it.  The dish look pretty appetizing.  She enjoyed it.tinyurl.com/aqqova8Receipt (Dinner for 2 - $110.64):tinyurl.com/b5us2cfOverall - Rushed service led to a rushed dining experience.  Nice spacious room.  Large US chain-level quality Tex-Mex food.  If you really have a hankerin' for some Tex-Mex or pseudo Mexican food, they will do.  So you do not get rushed out the door, I suggest going well before 10 pm.

X3Tq8RBNOYoJARZFXoug4w.text: This restaurant is located at Dempsey Hills and there are a few Mexican Restaurants nearby so it is easily missed.Arrived around 6.30 pm on a Thursday night. Parking was alright as there were still empty spots when I arrived. It will be more crowded around 7pm on weekdays and no doubt on weekends.It is my first time eating at a Mexican Restaurant in Singapore so I can't really compare yet (more reviews for the ones in California).When My aunt and I stepped indoor, there were reserved signs on most table. The servers did not really hear us out on wanting the indoor seat and had to repeat ourselves for three times before they gave us a corner table for two.Looking at the menu, there were a range of choices. I looked into the burrito section and spotted beef chimichanga. My aunt ordered something else.For drinks, I had a strawberry jarritos. Missed this soda ever since I stepped in Singapore. The food came 15 minutes later and came in a big portion. I was amazed at the portion and expected a smaller portion for a huge price ($18). The tortilla outside was crispy. The black bean with cheese was delicious but there are too much chunks of shredded beef. On my plate there was a side of rice and a side of cabbage/lettuce. The portion is too big for the taste. I would prefer less meat to savor the sour cream and the avocado instead. (1/2 star deducted here).We called for checks and it came to a more shocking amount. 7% gst, 10% service charge. In the end two meals, two drinks added up around $70+. I think that they need to cut down the price. (This is why 1/2 star is deducted).Overall it is alright to go there once awhile. But since there was no other reviews i was not sure what's good here.

photos.caption: Photo of Margarita's Dempsey Hill - Singapore, Singapore. Beef chimichanga

sONyp8sGSJUAdlQy3dH-IA.text: Mesmerizing ambiance. Food, nothing worth reviewing except being over-priced like many things in S'PoreMargaritas are good though!!!

Y-JRje4sIVngT3DuwolI2g.text: Always enjoy this place.  Authentic...not sexy mexican food.  Good selection if tequila.

RF30HX3WeaMeHBkbKq0zeQ.text: When I went there the first time, I picked it because it had the most crowd compared to its neighboring restaurants. When the dinner finished, we were certain that we had made the right decision. Since then, I went back a few times when I wanted to eat Mexican food. The business is always good, and there's lots of Mexican expats - a sign that the food is authentic perhaps? I highly recommend their Steak, done in the traditional Mexican way. It's very tender and juicy. Atmosphere is very classy. The food is pricey, but it's standard for Dempsey.
